Sinopse: Ellie O'Brien (List) is trying to juggle rhythmic gymnastics and troubles with her best friend. Meanwhile, classmate Jack Malloy (Bertrand) is struggling to live up to his brothers' hockey-star legacies and his dad's high expectations and tough-love approach. During a text argument about whose life is easier, Ellie and Jack trigger an inexplicable real-life swap. As each tries to navigate the other's life, hilarity ensues when Ellie, as Jack, learns about brotherly bonding and hockey lingo, while Jack, as Ellie, learns to decipher girl code and experiences a spa day. With a rhythmic gymnastics championship and a spot on the varsity hockey team on the line, they must figure out how to get back into their own bodies before the swap becomes permanent. As they are forced to literally walk in each other's shoes, they gain empathy for each other and learn valuable lessons about their own lives.—Disney Channel PR
